# Graph RAG

- Model entities and relationships explicitly before choosing a graph store (Neo4j, etc.).
- Extract entities/relations in a dedicated pipeline step; do not rely on the LLM to query raw graphs directly.
- Combine vector search (semantic similarity) with graph traversal (structural relevance).
- Limit graph traversal depth (2–3 hops) to control latency and context size.
- Serialize subgraphs to compact natural language or structured JSON for LLM context.
- Version graph schema and extraction prompts together.
- Evaluate retrieval with both factual QA and multi-hop reasoning benchmarks.
- Cache frequent subgraph queries; graph traversals can be expensive at scale.
- Handle missing edges gracefully — partial graphs are common in real data.
- Prefer hybrid retrieval: vector + keyword + graph when accuracy matters.
